rtgage%20Rates%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20increased%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-the-federal-funds-rate%5C%22%3Efederal%20funds%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20dramatically%20in%202022%20and%202023%20to%20try%20to%20slow%20economic%20growth%20and%20get%20inflation%20under%20control.%20Inflation%20has%20since%20slowed%20significantly%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20a%20bit%20above%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20aren't%20directly%20impacted%20by%20changes%20to%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%2C%20but%20they%20often%20trend%20up%20or%20down%20ahead%20of%20Fed%20policy%20moves.%20This%20is%20because%20mortgage%20rates%20change%20based%20on%20investor%20demand%20for%20mortgage-backed%20securities%2C%20and%20this%20demand%20is%20often%20impacted%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20policy%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20recently%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-cuts-interest-rates-how-much-september-fomc-powell-inflation-2024-9%5C%22%3Elower%20rates%20by%2050%20basis%20points%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mortgage%20rates%20trended%20down%20ahead%20of%20this%20decision.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Mortgage%20Rate%20Projection%20for%202024%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Rate%20Projection%20for%202024%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202025%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20drop%20much%20further%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20started%20ticking%20up%20from%20historic%20lows%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202021%20and%20increased%20dramatically%20in%202022%20and%20throughout%20most%20of%202023.%20But%20now%20that%20inflation%20has%20decelerated%20and%20the%20Fed%20is%20expected%20to%20cut%20rates%20soon%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20trended%20down.%20In%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-september-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%20rose%20by%202.4%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20significant%20slowdown%20compared%20to%20when%20it%20peaked%20at%209.1%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20rates%20go%20down%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves.%20If%20economic%20conditions%20remain%20stable%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20not%20fall%20as%20much.%20But%20if%20the%20labor%20market%20weakens%20and%20the%20Fed%20has%20to%20cut%20rates%20more%20aggressively%2C%20we%20could%20see%20rates%20drop%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20But%20we%20could%20see%20them%20settle%20in%20close%20to%205%25%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22When%20Will%20House%20Prices%20Come%20Down%3F%5C%22%3EWhen%20Will%20House%20Prices%20Come%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20aren't%20likely%20to%20see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhome-prices-drop%5C%22%3Ehome%20prices%20drop%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20In%20fact%2C%20they'll%20probably%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanniemae.com%2Fmedia%2F53421%2Fdisplay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFannie%20Mae%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20expect%20prices%20to%20increase%205.8%25%20in%202024%20and%203.6%25%20in%202025%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mba.org%2Fnews-and-research%2Fforecasts-and-commentary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Bankers%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20expects%20a%203.8%25%20increase%20in%202024%20a