0for.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERight%20before%20giving%20birth%2C%20I%20found%20out%20our%20second%20baby%2C%20a%20son%2C%20would%20have%20a%20space%20in%20the%20same%20day%20care%20center%20as%20my%20daughter.%20The%20catch%20was%20that%20the%20spot%20would%20open%20when%20he%20was%20only%20one%20week%20old.%20If%20we%20wanted%20to%20guarantee%20the%20spot%2C%20we%20would%20have%20to%20start%20paying%20for%20it%20then%2C%20so%20I%20started%20paying%20for%20him%20four%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-childcare-costs-in-us-women-workforce-cheapest-countries-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emonths%20before%20I%20went%20back%20to%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20couldn't%20believe%20I%20did%20it%20%E2%80%94%20paid%20for%20childcare%20I%20wasn't%20even%20using%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20would%20tell%20them%20there%20was%20no%20other%20option.%20He%20either%20wouldn't%20have%20care%2C%20or%20he%20would%20have%20been%20in%20a%20different%20facility%20from%20my%20daughter.%20Putting%20them%20in%20different%20centers%20would%20have%20been%20practically%20impossible%20for%20our%20family%2C%20given%20our%20work%20commutes%20and%20the%20pre-pandemic%20lack%20of%20flexibility%20for%20parents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2281e1dbb6-a55c-45a3-8a02-4e0fe199c866%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20cost%20of%20day%20care%20was%20double%20our%20monthly%20mortgage%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJust%20when%20we%20started%20to%20hang%20of%20paying%20a%20monthly%20bill%20for%20childcare%20that%20was%20twice%20the%20cost%20of%20my%20mortgage%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20my%20part-time%20business%20full-time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20major%20consideration%20in%20being%20able%20to%20quit%20my%20corporate%20job%20was%20whether%20we%20could%20afford%20day%20care%20if%20I%20did.%20We%20ultimately%20built%20up%20a%20savings%20account%20that%20would%20take%20us%20through%20six%20months%20of%20their%20day%20care%20tuition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20remember%20writing%20that%20first%20check%20to%20pay%20for%20two%20children.%20I%20handed%20it%20to%20the%20day%20care%20director%2C%20and%20it%20hurt.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20scariest%20moments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20years%2C%20we%20paid%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20for%20our%20two%20children%20to%20be%20taken%20care%20of%20while%20we%20worked.%20In%20the%202020%2F2021%20school%20year%2C%20we%20paid%20%2459%2C520%20in%20childcare%20costs.%20That%20was%20twice%20the%20amount%20I%20was%20paying%20for%20the%20mortgage.%20But%20this%20amount%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bmarket%20rate%26quot%3B%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20where%20the%20going%20rate%20for%20basic%20childcare%20is%20anywhere%20from%20%242%2C000%20to%20%242%2C700%20per%20child.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2277393d7d-50f6-4c0b-af97-4df0a364321d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20stopped%20paying%20when%20they%20got%20into%20public%20preschool%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20continued%20paying%20this%20amount%20the%20entire%20time%20both%20of%20my%20older%20children%20were%20in%20full-time%20either%20childcare%20or%20public%20school.%20When%20my%20daughter%20was%205%20and%20my%20son%203%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20access%20Universal%20Pre-K%2C%20leaving%20us%20to%20only%20pay%20for%20after-school%20childcare.%20You%20have%20to%20literally%20%26quot%3Blottery%20in%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20schools%20for%20Universal%20Pre-K%20and%20it's%20not%20available%20in%20all%20states.%20When%20you%20get%20it%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20you've%20won%20the%20jackpot.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20freedom%20of%20not%20paying%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20each%20year%20on%20childcare%20felt%20incredible.%20It%20was%20life-changing.%20We%20were%20able%20to%20move%20from%20our%20two-bedroom%20house%20to%20something%20a%20little%20bigger%20because%20we%20knew%20that%20a%20huge%20portion%20of%20our%20income%20would%20be%20freed%20up%2C%20and%20we%20could%20save%20more%20money%20for%20the%20kids%20to%20go%20to%20college.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20there%20were%20several%20reasons%20we%20decided%20to%20wait%20to%20have%20our%20third%20baby%2C%20childcare%20costs%20were%20one%20of%20the%20factors.%20It%20would%20have%20been%20financially%20impossible%20to%20have%20three%20kids%20in%20full-time%20childcare.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229ab31146-8164-46c1-b440-6e42990e4894%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20enjoy%20working%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20spoke%20about%20the%20price%20of%20childcare%20on%20social%20media%2C%20some%20people%20questioned%20why%20I%20hadn't%20decided%20to%20stay%20home%20with%20them%20to%20avoid%20the%20cost%20of%20childcare.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20motherhood%20penalty%20was%20on%20my%20radar.%20It's%20a%20phenomenon%20in%20which%20women's%20wages%20stagnate%20or%20decrease%20during%20childbearing%20years.%20They%20either%20leave%20the%20workforce%20and%20come%20back%20later%2C%20which%20impacts%20their%20long-term%20potential%2C%20or%20they%20stay%20on%20and%20are%20perceived%20as%20less%20committed.%20I%20didn't%20want%20that%20to%20be%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20also%20saw%20the%20long-term%20value%20of%20spending%20huge%20amounts%20of%20my%20salary%20on%20childcare.%20Even%20if%20everything%20I%20made%20was%20going%20back%20out%20on%20childcare%2C%20I%20was%20still%20saving%20in%20my%20401(k)%20and%20would%20have%20much%20more%20money%20over%20the%20course%20of%20my%20lifetime.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20most%20importantly%2C%20I%20love%20my%20job.%20I%20want%20to%20keep%20doing%20it%20while%20also%20parenting%2C%20and%20this%20shouldn't%20be%20just%20a%20privilege.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%