le%20to%20slow%20the%20Russian%20advance%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellite-images-show-destroyed-russian-bridges-kursk-after-ukrainian-strikes-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethrough%20steps%20like%20blowing%20up%20bridges%3C%2Fa%3E%20critical%20for%20moving%20in%20troops%2C%20weapons%2C%20and%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Russia%20has%20taken%20back%2046%25%20of%20what%20Ukraine%20once%20held%20in%20Kursk%2C%20the%20US-based%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%20said%20in%20an%20update%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20citing%20visual%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d5ecdea-93b6-4f29-9899-d4ef06689399%5C%22%3EA%20harder%20fight%20for%20Russia%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20forces%20have%20options%20for%20defending%20and%20moving%20in%20Kursk%20that%20typically%20only%20Russian%20soldiers%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20had%20in%20this%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20flexibility.%20Unlike%20at%20home%2C%20where%20Ukraine%20fights%20to%20defend%20all%20of%20its%20territory%2C%20inside%20Russia%2C%20it%20can%20be%20more%20mobile%20and%20strategically%20give%20up%20some%20land%20to%20better%20defend%20the%20areas%20it%20can%20really%20hold%20or%20wants%20to%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Bohnert%2C%20a%20warfare%20expert%20at%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20told%20BI%20Ukraine%20doesn't%20have%20to%20defend%20Russian%20cities.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20fight%20where%20it's%20advantageous%20and%20pull%20back%20when%20it's%20not.%20And%20that's%20a%20really%20efficient%20way%20of%20fighting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20how%20much%20of%20the%20territory%20that%20Russia%20took%20back%20was%20deliberately%20given%20up%20by%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20experts%20say%20they%20never%20expected%20Ukraine%20to%20hold%20all%20of%20the%20territory%20that%20it%20it%20seized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20someone%20might%20look%20at%20the%20recent%20advances%20and%20say%20they're%20big%2C%20I%20would%20also%20say%20it's%20because%20Ukraine%20just%20took%20so%20much%20territory%2C%20more%20than%20they%20even%20intended%20to%20defend%2C%26quot%3B%20Alberque%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20very%20easy%20now%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20do%20some%20sort%20of%20fighting%20retreats%20and%20seed%20territory%20that%20they%20could%20never%20legitimately%20hold%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20initial%20reaction%20to%20Ukraine's%20unexpected%20incursion%20was%20slow%20and%20messy.%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2024%2F08%2F18%2Fvladimir-putin-kursk-crisis-reponse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efroze%20at%20first%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20eventually%20put%20the%20FSB%20%E2%80%94%20Russia's%20security%20and%20intelligence%20agency%20%E2%80%94%20in%20charge%20of%20a%20complicated%20response%20involving%20other%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227715%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20walks%20past%20a%20car%20in%20a%20ruined%20neighborhood.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d7449314a5cd1fcc8cbb31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225143%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20walks%20past%20a%20car%20in%20Sudzha%2C%20in%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20time%20gave%20Ukraine%20a%20certain%20defensive%20advantage%2C%20experts%20said%2C%20though%20it%20is%20unclear%20to%20what%20extent%20Ukraine%20leveraged%20that%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20always%20thought%20that%20if%20Russia%20attacked%20much%2C%20much%20more%20quickly%20against%20the%20Ukrainian%20salient%2C%20Ukraine%20would've%20withdrawn%20more%20quickly%2C%26quot%3B%20Alberque%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESavill%20said%20Russia's%20botched%20response%20has%20enabled%20the%20Ukrainians%20%26quot%3Bto%20hold